# NovaLang Pronunciation Profiles Gateway

Status: `JAPANESE_LANGUAGE_PROFILE_EXISTS` ·
`ROMANIZATION_IMPLEMENTATION_PASS` · `ADR_015_APPROVED_FROZEN` ·
`JAPANESE_FULL_PROFILE_CLOSED_FROZEN`

Apply this gateway after `AGENTS.md` and `.cursor/rules/novalang.mdc`. It
defines the global contract; detailed linguistic rules live only in
[`rules/languages/`](../../rules/languages/README.md).

## Global contract

Keep these fields separate: `surfaceText`, `reading`, `romanization`,
`pronunciation`, and `ttsText`. `reading` is literal in the language's
phonetic system. `romanization` is learner-facing Latin transliteration.
`ttsText` defaults to native script and never to `romanization`.

Every learning language needs an approved `PronunciationProfile` before its
first real lesson enters production. Contextual rules must be evidence-based,
must not be blind character substitution, and must preserve approved content
overrides with a reason/source. Missing analysis must fail loudly or require
an explicit override.

## Canonical language sources

- [Japanese (`ja`)](../../rules/languages/ja/README.md): complete pilot rules,
  currently `JAPANESE_LANGUAGE_PROFILE_EXISTS`, `APPROVED / FROZEN`, with
  native expert review explicitly `WAIVED / NOT_COMPLETED` by Project Owner.
- [_template](../../rules/languages/_template/README.md): architecture for a
  future language; it contains no invented linguistic rules.

ADR-015 is the architecture record. Implementation files and fixtures are
referenced by the applicable language directory; this gateway deliberately
does not duplicate Japanese spelling, particle, romanization, or TTS details.
